The Benue State Governor, Samuel Ortom has condoled with the family of Abubakar Tsav over the death of the former Lagos State Police Commissioner. Ortom expressed shock over Tsav’s sudden death. Tsav had died at the Federal Medical Centre, Makurdi, Benue State on Monday afternoon. Reacting to his death, Ortom described Tsav as a gallant police officer while in service. A statement by the governor’s spokesman, Tever Akase reads: “Governor Samuel Ortom, on behalf of the Benue State Government, sends heartfelt condolences to the family of former Lagos State Police Commissioner, Alhaji Abubakar Tsav over his death earlier today. “The Governor expresses shock at the demise of Alhaji Tsav whom he describes as a gallant police officer during his years in service. “He prays God to grant the deceased eternal rest and his family the fortitude to bear the loss.”